nd keyword [frontend] in Trace data, indicating latency anomalies (e.g., \'frontend->checkoutservice\' in trace analysis findings from Full Context). Step 4: Derive Root Cause - Based on the observed metric anomalies (rrt and rrt_max spikes) and trace patterns (frontend involvement), determined cause is the key metrics including rrt and rrt_max fault, per Ground Truth key_metrics.\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Metric: Search for metric [rrt] in the collected metric data and check for significant changes between normal and fault medians.\\nCheck Metric: Search for metric [rrt_max] in the metric data and identify instances with high change rates (e.g., >1.9).\\nCheck Trace: Search for keyword \'frontend\' in trace data to detect affected services and operation delays, especially in latency anomaly entries.",\n    "Fault Type: rrt, rrt_max, request, response, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets\\nSymptom: Packet corruption and data corruption on the network causing bit errors and corrupted packets, leading to service connection failures and latency spikes.\\nRoot Cause: Component cartservice experienced rrt, rrt_max, request, response, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is cartservice (from Ground Truth instance list, with cartservice selected based on Full Context evidence). Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword \'Error while dialing\' in Log, specifically in log entries: \'transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 10.233.46.196:7070: i/o timeout\' (from Full Context filtered_logs). Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword \'rrt\' and \'rrt_max\' in Metric, with abnormal increases: e.g., cartservice-1 rrt_max increased 2750x from 37.7s to 22,501s (from Full Context metric_analysis_findings). Step 4: Check Observation - Found keyword \'timeout\' 